         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24 February 1866. ¶  ¶ It ¶  ¶ has ¶  ¶ pleased me immeasurably, esteemed Professor, that you use your continued mighty advocacy for the movement in search of Leichhardt. ¶ The Ladies' Leichhardt Sear...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">66.02.24f</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To August Petermann</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">SPA ARCH<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">PGM<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">328</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Petermann: 'Erh. 13. April 1866' [Received 13 April 1866].<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>For a published version of this letter,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see Voigt (1996),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 77.</p>
               </note>24/2/66</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es hat mich unendlich gefreut, verehrter Herr Professor, dass Sie der Bewegung für die Aufsuchung Leichhardt Ihre fortgesetzte mächtige Fürsprache zuwenden. Bei Ihrem regen Interesse für das Unternehmen wird es erfreulich sein für Sie zu hören, dass M'Intyre einstweilen die Wüste hinter sich zurückliess, u. mit einer neu organisirten Parthie den Thomson-Fluss erreichte. Unglücklicherweise verlor er nahe 70 Pferde aus Wassermangel; doch sind die Dromedare alle gerettet; u da er sich nun in den tropischen Breiten bewegt, wird er nicht wieder zu leiden haben es sei denn gegen den Westen des Continents hin. Es gebrach uns an Mitteln die Kameele u Pferde nebst dem nöthigen Futter mit Schiffen zum Carpentaria-Golf zu senden.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Der berühmte Dr Barth zählt jetzt ja denn auch zu den Todten! — Erst vor wenigen Wochen sicherte er mir seine Theilnahme an der Förderung des Unternehmens für Leichhardt zu, u. versprach diese Sache der Damen in der Gesellschaft der Geographen in Berlin zu befürworten. Gewiss wird der Nachfolger Barths der Unternehmung gleiche Gunst zuwenden.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Verehrungsvoll<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24 February 1866.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>pleased me immeasurably, esteemed Professor, that you use your continued mighty advocacy for the movement in search of Leichhardt.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Ladies' Leichhardt Search Expedition,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1865-6.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>With your lively interest in the enterprise you will be pleased to hear, that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in the meantime<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M'Intyre<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Duncan McIntyre.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has left the desert behind and has reached the Thomson River<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Qld.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with his re-organised party. Unfortunately he lost nearly 70 horses due to lack of water,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to A. Petermann, 26 January 1866<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 66-01-26a), with M's confidential unofficial version of events leading to the loss of the horses.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but all the dromedaries are saved;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as he now moves through the tropical latitudes, he should not have to suffer any more, except perhaps towards the west of the continent. We lacked the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>funds to transport the camels and horses together with the necessary fodder to the Gulf of Carpentaria by ship.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>So the famous Dr Barth is also<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>numbered<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>among the dead now! — Only a few weeks ago he assured me of his participation in the promotion of the enterprise for Leichhardt, and promised to recommend this<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>quest of the ladies to the Society for Geography in Berlin.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Gesellschaft für Erdkunde zu Berlin.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I am sure<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that Barth's successor will bestow the same favour on the venture.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
